# Responsive Design Requirements

## Principle

**All layouts must work on both desktop and mobile devices.** Use responsive design patterns, flexible layouts, and mobile-first approaches. Implement responsive dropdown menus and adaptive layouts.

## Rationale

- **Accessibility**: Users access the site from various devices
- **User Experience**: Mobile-friendly sites provide better UX
- **Modern Web Standards**: Responsive design is expected
- **SEO**: Mobile-friendly sites rank better
- **Future-Proof**: Adapts to new device sizes automatically

## Implementation Guidelines

### Layout Responsiveness

1. **Use Flexible Units**: Prefer relative units (rem, em, %, vw, vh) over fixed pixels
   ```css
   /* ❌ BAD - Fixed width */
   .container { width: 1200px; }
   
   /* ✅ GOOD - Flexible width */
   .container { max-width: 87.5rem; width: 97%; }
   ```

2. **Flexbox/Grid for Layouts**: Use flexbox or CSS Grid for responsive layouts
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Responsive flexbox */
   .row {
     display: flex;
     flex-wrap: wrap;
   }
   
   .col-md-4 {
     flex: 0 0 33.333333%;
     max-width: 33.333333%;
   }
   ```

3. **Media Queries**: Use breakpoints for different screen sizes
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Responsive breakpoints */
   @media (max-width: 61.9375rem) {
     .col-md-4 {
       flex: 0 0 50%;
       max-width: 50%;
     }
   }
   
   @media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
     .col-md-4 {
       flex: 0 0 100%;
       max-width: 100%;
     }
   }
   ```

### Navigation Responsiveness

1. **Mobile Menu**: Convert horizontal nav to dropdown/hamburger menu on mobile
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Responsive navigation */
   @media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
     ul#nav {
       float: none;
       clear: both;
     }
     
     ul#nav li {
       width: 33%;
       text-align: center;
     }
   }
   ```

2. **Touch-Friendly Targets**: Ensure interactive elements are large enough for touch
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Touch-friendly button */
   .carousel-btn {
     width: 3.125rem;
     height: 3.125rem;
   }
   
   @media (max-width: 48rem) {
     .carousel-btn {
       width: 2.5rem;
       height: 2.5rem;
     }
   }
   ```

3. **Dropdown Menus**: Implement responsive dropdown behavior
   - Desktop: Hover to show dropdown
   - Mobile: Click/tap to toggle dropdown
   - Use JavaScript for mobile interactions if needed

### Image Responsiveness

1. **Flexible Images**: Images should scale with container
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Responsive images */
   img {
     max-width: 100%;
     height: auto;
   }
   ```

2. **Responsive Sizing**: Adjust image sizes for different screens
   ```css
   .carousel-slide img {
     max-width: 70%;
   }
   
   @media (max-width: 48rem) {
     .carousel-slide img {
       max-width: 85%;
     }
   }
   ```

### Typography Responsiveness

1. **Relative Font Sizes**: Use rem/em units that scale with base font size
   ```css
   /* ✅ GOOD - Relative sizing */
   html { font-size: 16px; }
   h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
   p { font-size: 1rem; }
   ```

2. **Readable on Mobile**: Ensure text is readable without zooming
   - Minimum font size: 0.875rem (14px) for body text
   - Adequate line-height for readability

### Breakpoint Strategy

Use consistent breakpoints:
- **Mobile**: max-width: 47.9375rem (767px)
- **Tablet**: max-width: 61.9375rem (991px)
- **Desktop**: Above 991px

### Testing Requirements

1. **Test on Multiple Devices**: Verify layout works on:
   - Desktop (1920px, 1366px)
   - Tablet (768px, 1024px)
   - Mobile (375px, 414px, 320px)

2. **Test Interactions**: Ensure:
   - Navigation works on touch devices
   - Buttons are tappable
   - Forms are usable
   - Content is readable

### Common Patterns

1. **Mobile-First Approach**: Start with mobile styles, enhance for desktop
   ```css
   /* Base styles for mobile */
   .container { padding: 0.625rem; }
   
   /* Enhance for desktop */
   @media (min-width: 48rem) {
     .container { padding: 1.25rem; }
   }
   ```

2. **Hide/Show Elements**: Show/hide content based on screen size
   ```css
   .desktop-only { display: block; }
   .mobile-only { display: none; }
   
   @media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
     .desktop-only { display: none; }
     .mobile-only { display: block; }
   }
   ```

3. **Stack on Mobile**: Stack columns vertically on mobile
   ```css
   .row {
     display: flex;
     flex-direction: row;
   }
   
   @media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
     .row {
       flex-direction: column;
     }
   }
   ```

## Examples

### ✅ GOOD - Responsive Navigation
```css
ul#nav {
  float: right;
  list-style: none;
}

@media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
  ul#nav {
    float: none;
    clear: both;
  }
  
  ul#nav li {
    width: 33%;
    text-align: center;
  }
}
```

### ✅ GOOD - Responsive Grid
```css
.col-md-4 {
  flex: 0 0 33.333333%;
  max-width: 33.333333%;
}

@media (max-width: 61.9375rem) {
  .col-md-4 {
    flex: 0 0 50%;
    max-width: 50%;
  }
}

@media (max-width: 47.9375rem) {
  .col-md-4 {
    flex: 0 0 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Fixed Width Layout
```css
.container { width: 1200px; }
.nav { width: 800px; }
/* No media queries - breaks on mobile */
```

## Checklist

When implementing layouts:
- [ ] Does it work on mobile (375px width)?
- [ ] Does it work on tablet (768px width)?
- [ ] Does it work on desktop (1920px width)?
- [ ] Are navigation elements touch-friendly?
- [ ] Are images responsive?
- [ ] Is text readable without zooming?
- [ ] Are breakpoints consistent?
- [ ] Are dropdown menus responsive?
- [ ] Is layout flexible (uses flexbox/grid)?
- [ ] Are units relative (rem/em/%) not fixed (px)?

## Goal

**Every layout must be fully functional and visually appropriate on all device sizes from 320px to 2560px+.** No horizontal scrolling, no broken layouts, no unreadable text.
